oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Newlyweds
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Edwin Best
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Greenback (Tenn.);
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Two couples in a studio prop designed to look like the end of a train. A striped awning is above them. Signs on the prop say "Leaving St. Louis. Bound for the West," "Bound for Sterling, Colo" and "Burlington Route." The men wear suits and a tie or bowtie. The women wear dresses with hats. The newlyweds are leaving to look for work in Colorado.
